<p>
    <strong>Stafford </strong>
</p>
<p>
    First; to qualify the student has to be enrolled at least half time.
</p>
<p>
    Stafford Loans come in several variables, subsidized and unsubsidized. Subsidized loans do not accrue interest until the student begins repayment; the
    current rate is 3.4%. Unsubsidized loans accrue interest from the date college begins; the current rate is 6.8%. A student is offered a subsidized Stafford
    loan depending on the results of the completion of the FAFSA. There are no income or credit requirements for the unsubsidized Stafford Loan.
</p>
<p>
    Another variation is whether or not the student is determined to be a Dependent student or Independent Student. The defining characteristics are quite
    black and white and can be seen <a target="_blank" href="/member/private_file/dependentindependent">here</a>
</p>
<p>
    <strong>IMPORTANT NOTE:</strong>
    If the parent is denied for a PLUS loan, which does have credit underwriting, the Dependent loan limits are the same as the higher Independent loan limits.
</p>
